\section*{Solving the Intervalley Transition Rate Equation}

The solution of the intervalley transition rate equation is activated by adding the keyword eMVTransitionRate or hMVTransitionRate to the Coupled\{\} statement in the Solve\{\} section:
```
Solve {
    ...
    Coupled {Poisson Electron eMVTransitionRate}
    ...
}
```

[Page 354 END]
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


The following example shows the necessary setting to solve the transition rate equations between the two valleys \(\Gamma\) and \(L\) for GaAs using the Müller transition rate model. In the Physics section, multivalley statistics must be activated and the transition rate models are defined:
```
Physics {
    ...
    eMultiValley
    eTransitionRate(
        Transition "1" (
            Model = "MuellerGammaL"
            ParameterSetName = "MuellerParams"
            FromToValleyPairs = ("Gamma", "L")
            DrivingForce = "ElectricField"
        )
        Transition "2" (
            Model = "MuellerLGamma"
            ParameterSetName = "MuellerParams"
            FromToValleyPairs = ("L", "Gamma")
            DrivingForce = "ElectricField"
        )
    )
    ...
}
```


Two transitions are defined. The first one models the transition from the \(\Gamma\)-valley to the \(L\)-valley using the model described in Equation 216, and the second one models the transition in the opposite direction using the model described in Equation 217. The electric field is chosen as the driving force for both models.

In the Solve section, the keyword eMVTransitionRate is added to the Coupled\{\} statement to allow for the solution of the transition rate equation:
```
Solve {
    Coupled {Poisson}
    Coupled {Poisson Electron eMVTransitionRate}
}
```


The explicit valley densities can be plotted by adding the eDensity_valleyname or hDensity_valleyname in the Plot section:
```
Plot {
    eDensity_Gamma
    eDensity_L
}
```

[Page 355 END]
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Finally, the correct multivalley setup must be provided in the parameter file (Using Multivalley Band Structure on page 346) together with the model parameters for the Müller transition rate model:
```
MultiValley {
    eValley"Gamma"(m=0.067, alpha=1.0, degeneracy=1)
    eValley"L"(m=0.8, energy=0.2, alpha=0.5, degeneracy=4)
}
TRM_Mueller "MuellerParams" {
    af_ivt = 0.36e12, //[Hz]
    EO_ivt = 3.0e3, //[V/cm]
    NO_ivt = 78.6e16, //[cm-3]
    zeta_ivt = 0.46, //[1]
    f0_ivt = 1.7e12 //[Hz]
    deltaF_ivt = 5.79e6 //[Hz/(V/cm)]
}
