\end{table}

In some special cases, it might be necessary to deactivate the default constant mobility. This can be accomplished by specifying the -ConstantMobility option to Mobility:
```
Physics { Mobility ( -ConstantMobility ... ) ... }
```


In Equation 261, the exponent of the temperature \((\zeta)\) is a constant, which corresponds to the default behavior. For a more accurate treatment of mobility as a function of temperature (particularly, mobility at low temperatures), the exponent becomes a function of temperature itself. For more details, see Low-Temperature Phonon Exponent Correction for Mobility Models on page 453 and Constant Mobility Model on page 454.

