\section*{Arora Model}

The Arora model [3] reads:
\[
\mu_{\mathrm{dop}}=\mu_{\min }+\frac{\mu_{\mathrm{d}}}{1+\left(\left(N_{\mathrm{A}, 0}+N_{\mathrm{D}, 0}\right) / N_{0}\right)^{A^{*}}}
\]
with:
\[
\mu_{\min }=A_{\min } \cdot\left(\frac{T}{300 \mathrm{~K}}\right)^{\alpha_{\mathrm{m}}} \quad, \quad \mu_{\mathrm{d}}=A_{\mathrm{d}} \cdot\left(\frac{T}{300 \mathrm{~K}}\right)^{\alpha_{\mathrm{d}}}
\]
and:
\[
N_{0}=A_{N} \cdot\left(\frac{T}{300 \mathrm{~K}}\right)^{\alpha_{N}} \quad, \quad A^{*}=A_{\mathrm{a}} \cdot\left(\frac{T}{300 \mathrm{~K}}\right)^{\alpha_{\mathrm{a}}}
\]

The parameters are accessible in the DopingDependence parameter set in the parameter file.

