\section*{Multivalley Transferred Electron Mobility}

This experimental model accounts for the transferred electron effect in III-V applications based on the usage of the Sentaurus Device hydrodynamic model (see Hydrodynamic Model for Temperatures on page 267) and the multivalley band-structure representation (see Multivalley Band Structure on page 342). For a description of the model and its settings, see Multivalley Transferred Carrier Mobility Model on page 997.

\section*{Explicit Multivalley Mobility Model}

Compared to the transferred electron mobility models (Transferred Electron Model and Transferred Electron Model 2) or the multivalley transferred electron mobility model (Multivalley Transferred Electron Mobility), the explicit multivalley mobility model allows for a more physical description of the transferred electron effect by using the dynamic non-equilibrium valley densities computed by solving the transition rate equation described in Solving the Intervalley Transition Rate Equation on page 354.

In the explicit multivalley mobility model, a weighted average based on the individual valley densities are computed. This means that, for electrons (it is analogous for holes), the total mobility is calculated as:
\[
\mu_{\mathrm{tot}}=\frac{1}{n_{\mathrm{tot}}} \sum_{i}^{N_{n}} \mu_{i} n_{i}
\]
where \(n_{j}\) is the density, \(\mu_{i}\) is the mobility value computed for valley \(i, N_{n}\) is the number of valleys, and \(n_{\text {tot }}\) is the total density that is the solution of the continuity equation.

To activate the explicit multivalley mobility model, specify MultiValley in the Mobility section. In the following example:
```
eMobility(MultiValley, ConstantMobility, HighFieldSaturation)
```

the expression in Equation 261 together with the expression in Equation 362 are evaluated to calculate the valley-specific mobility values, which are then finally combined as shown in Equation 367.

In the parameter file, the mobility parameters per valley must be present as named parameter sets. For example:
```
MultiValley {
    eValley"Gamma"(m=0.067 alpha=1.0 degeneracy=1)
    eValley"L"(m=0.85 energy=0.28448214 alpha=0.5 degeneracy=4)
}
ConstantMobility "eValley_Gamma" {...}
ConstantMobility "eValley_L" {...}
HighFieldDependence "eValley_Gamma" {...}
HighFieldDependence "eValley_L" {...}
```

