\section*{Trap-Assisted Auger Recombination Model}

The trap-assisted Auger (TAA) recombination model is a modification of the SRH recombination and coupled defect level recombination models (see Shockley-Read-Hall Recombination on page 493 and Coupled Defect Level Recombination on page 507).

When TAA is active, Sentaurus Device uses the lifetimes [4]:
\[
\begin{gathered}
\frac{\tau_{p}}{1+\tau_{p} / \tau_{p}^{\mathrm{TAA}}} \\
\frac{\tau_{n}}{1+\tau_{n} / \tau_{n}^{\mathrm{TAT}}}
\end{gathered}
\]
instead of the lifetimes \(\tau_{p}\) and \(\tau_{n}\) in Equation 405 and Equation 446.
The TAA lifetimes in Equation 438 depend on the carrier densities:
\[
\begin{aligned}
& \frac{1}{\tau_{n}^{\mathrm{TAA}}} \approx C_{p}^{\mathrm{TAA}}(n+p) \\
& \frac{1}{\tau_{p}^{\mathrm{TAA}}} \approx C_{n}^{\mathrm{TAA}}(n+p)
\end{aligned}
\]

A reasonable order of magnitude for the TAA coefficients \(C_{n}^{\text {TAA }}\) and \(C_{p}^{\text {TAA }}\) is \(1 \times 10^{-12} \mathrm{~cm}^{3} \mathrm{~s}^{-1}\) to \(1 \times 10^{-11} \mathrm{~cm}^{3} \mathrm{~s}^{-1}\); the defaults are \(C_{n}^{\mathrm{TAA}}=C_{p}^{\mathrm{TAA}}=1 \times 10^{-12} \mathrm{~cm}^{3} \mathrm{~s}^{-1}\).
TAA recombination is activated by using the keyword TrapAssistedAuger in the Recombination statement in the Physics section (see Table 242 on page 1680):
```
Physics {
    Recombination(TrapAssistedAuger ...)
    ...
}
```


The trap-assisted Auger parameters \(C_{n}^{\mathrm{TAA}}\) and \(C_{p}^{\mathrm{TAA}}\) are accessible in the parameter set TrapAssistedAuger.

