\section*{Okuto-Crowell Model}

Okuto and Crowell [20] suggested the empirical model:
\[
\alpha\left(F_{\mathrm{ava}}\right)=a \cdot\left(1+c\left(T-T_{0}\right)\right) F_{\mathrm{ava}}^{\gamma} \exp \left[-\left(\frac{b\left[1+d\left(T-T_{0}\right)\right]}{F_{\mathrm{ava}}}\right)^{\delta}\right]
\]
where \(T_{0}=300 \mathrm{~K}\) and Table 91 lists the user-adjustable parameters with their default values for silicon.

These values apply to the range of the electric field from \(10^{5} \mathrm{Vcm}^{-1}\) to \(10^{6} \mathrm{Vcm}^{-1}\).

[Page 518 END]
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Avalanche Generation

If BandgapDependence is specified as an argument to Avalanche, then the coefficient \(b\) in Equation 468 is replaced with:
