\section*{Avalanche Breakdown Probability}

For the simulation of single-photon avalanche diodes, knowledge of the avalanche breakdown probability is useful. Sentaurus Device can compute the electron \(P_{\mathrm{e}}(r)\), the hole \(P_{\mathrm{h}}(r)\), and the joint \(P_{\mathrm{j}}(r)\) avalanche breakdown probability according to the model of McIntyre [29].

The joint avalanche breakdown probability along the electric field line \(s(r)\) is given by:
\[
P_{\mathrm{j}}(s)=\frac{P_{\mathrm{h}}(0) f(s)}{P_{\mathrm{h}}(0) f(s)+1-P_{\mathrm{h}}(0)}
\]
where \(f(s)=\exp \left[\int_{0}^{s}\left(\alpha_{\mathrm{e}}-\alpha_{\mathrm{h}}\right) d s^{\prime}\right]\). Sentaurus Device solves the following line integrals along electric field lines in the multiplication region:
\[
\begin{aligned}
& -\log \left[1-P_{\mathrm{h}}(0)\right]=\int_{0}^{w} \alpha_{\mathrm{h}}(s) P_{\mathrm{j}}(s) d s \\
& 1-P_{\mathrm{h}}(s)=\left(1-P_{\mathrm{h}}(0)\right) \exp \left[\int_{0}^{s} \alpha_{\mathrm{h}}\left(s^{\prime}\right) P_{\mathrm{j}}\left(s^{\prime}\right) d s^{\prime}\right]
\end{aligned}
\]

The multiplication region is defined as the region where the electric field is higher than a threshold value. Outside the multiplication region, \(P_{\mathrm{e}}(r)=P_{\mathrm{h}}(r)=P_{\mathrm{j}}(r)=0\).

