\section*{Band-to-Band Tunneling Models}

Sentaurus Device provides different band-to-band tunneling models:
- Schenk Band-to-Band Tunneling Model on page 547
- Hurkx Band-to-Band Tunneling Model on page 548
- Modified Hurkx Band-to-Band Tunneling Model on page 549
- Simple Band-to-Band Tunneling Models on page 550
- Dynamic Nonlocal Path Band-to-Band Tunneling Model on page 550

The Schenk, Hurkx, modified Hurkx, and simple models use a common approach to suppress artificial band-to-band tunneling near insulator interfaces and for rapidly varying fields (see Tunneling Near Interfaces and Equilibrium Regions on page 546).

