\section*{Schenk Density Correction}

The modified electron density reads:
\[
\tilde{n}=n\left(\frac{n_{\mathrm{i}, \mathrm{eff}}}{N_{\mathrm{C}}}\right)^{\frac{\gamma_{n}\left|\nabla E_{\mathrm{F}, n}\right|}{F}}
\]

There is a similar relation for \(\tilde{p}\). The parameters \(\gamma_{n}=n /\left(n+n_{\text {ref }}\right)\) and \(\gamma_{p}=p /\left(p+p_{\text {ref }}\right)\) work as discussed in Density Correction for Schenk and Hurkx Trap-Assisted Tunneling Models on page 501. The reference densities \(n_{\text {ref }}\) and \(p_{\text {ref }}\) are specified (in \(\mathrm{cm}^{-3}\) ) by the DenCorRef parameter pair in the Band2BandTunneling parameter set.

An additional parameter MinGradQF (specified in \(\mathrm{eV} \mathrm{cm}^{-1}\) ) is available for smoothing at small values of the gradient for the Fermi potential.

\section*{Hurkx Band-to-Band Tunneling Model}

Similar to the other band-to-band tunneling models, in the Hurkx model [31], tunneling carriers are modeled by an additional generation-recombination process.

Its contribution is expressed as:
\[
R_{\text {net }}^{\mathrm{bb}}=A \cdot D \cdot\left(\frac{F}{1 \mathrm{~V} / \mathrm{cm}}\right)^{P} \exp \left(-\frac{B E_{\mathrm{g}}(T)^{3 / 2}}{E_{\mathrm{g}}(300 \mathrm{~K})^{3 / 2} F}\right)
\]
where:
\[
D=\frac{n p-n_{\mathrm{i}, \text { eff }}^{2}}{\left(n+n_{\mathrm{i}, \text { eff }}\right)\left(p+n_{\mathrm{i}, \text { eff }}\right)}(1-|\alpha|)+\alpha
\]

Here, specifying \(\alpha=0\) gives the original Hurkx model, whereas \(\alpha=-1\) gives only generation ( \(D=-1\) ), and \(\alpha=1\) gives only recombination ( \(D=1\) ). Therefore, if \(D<0\), it is a net carrier generation model. If \(D>0\), it is a recombination model. For Fermi statistics and quantization, Equation 505 is modified in the same way as for SRH recombination (see Equation 409).
For DensityCorrection=Local, \(n\) and \(p\) in Equation 505 are replaced by \(\tilde{n}\) and \(\tilde{p}\) (see Schenk Density Correction on page 548).
You can specify the coefficients \(A\) (in \(\mathrm{cm}^{-3} \mathrm{~s}^{-1}\) ), \(B\) (in \(\mathrm{V} / \mathrm{cm}\) ), \(P\), and \(\alpha\) in the parameter set Band2BandTunneling. By default, Sentaurus Device uses \(\alpha=0\) and the parameters from the E2 model (see Table 99 on page 550). Different values for the generation (Agen, Bgen, and Pgen) and recombination (Arec, Brec, and Prec) of carriers are supported.

For example, to change the parameters to those used in [31], use:
```
Band2BandTunneling {
    Agen = 4e14 # [1/( cm}3\textrm{s)]
    Bgen = 1.9e7 # [V/cm]
```

