\section*{Insulator Fixed Charges}

Sentaurus Device supports fixed charges in insulators and at insulator interfaces. Insulator fixed charges are defined with the keyword FixedCharge in the Physics-Traps section:
```
Physics (Material="Oxide"){
    Traps(
        (FixedCharge
            SpatialShape = [Gaussian | Uniform]
            Conc = <float> # [cm-3]
            SpaceMid = <vector> # [um]
            SpaceSig = <vector> # [um]
        )
    )
}
```


This syntax applies similarly to MaterialInterface, Region, and RegionInterface.
The keyword Conc specifies the maximum bulk or interface concentration of fixed charges in \(\mathrm{cm}^{-3}\) or \(\mathrm{cm}^{-2}\), respectively. The SpaceMid and SpaceSig keywords have the same meaning as for traps (see Energetic and Spatial Distribution of Traps on page 565). They are optional for uniform spatial distributions but mandatory for Gaussian spatial distributions.

