By default, index 6 or index 7 can result in the unwanted generation of electron or hole traps. This is because the capture rates are not linked to the channel charge concentrations. You can indirectly link index 6 and index 7 to the channel concentration by using eForce or hForce in the parameter file. For example, if eForce \(=1\), then the capture rate is computed only if the electron concentration is greater than the hole concentration on a vertex along the interface. This allows for the capture of electrons in NFETs only under positive gate bias conditions but with fixed n 0 .

