electron system at point \(u\) due to tunneling to and from the \(v\)-th shifted conduction band at point \(l<u\) is:
\[
H_{\mathrm{Pelt}, \mathrm{CC}, v}(u, l, \varepsilon)=\left[E_{\mathrm{C}}\left(u^{+}\right)-\varepsilon\right]\left[R_{\mathrm{CC}, v}(u, l, \varepsilon)-G_{\mathrm{CC}, v}(u, l, \varepsilon)\right]
\]
where \(u^{+}\)is infinitesimally larger than \(u\). Equation 852 vanishes everywhere except at abrupt jumps of the band edge. The Peltier part of the heat generation in the electron system at point \(l\) due to tunneling from the conduction band at \(u>l\) obeys an equation similar to Equation 852 , with \(E_{\mathrm{C}}\left(u^{+}\right)-\varepsilon\) replaced by \(\varepsilon-E_{\mathrm{C}}\left(l^{-}\right)\).
When the Band2Band option is used (see Table 247 on page 1685), Sentaurus Device also takes into account the band-to-band terms of the Peltier part of the heat generation at point \(u\) :
\[
H_{\mathrm{Pelt}, \mathrm{CV}, \mathrm{v}}(u, l, \varepsilon)=\left[E_{\mathrm{V}}\left(u^{+}\right)-\varepsilon\right]\left[R_{\mathrm{CV}, \mathrm{v}}(u, l, \varepsilon)-G_{\mathrm{CV}, \mathrm{v}}(u, l, \varepsilon)\right]
\]
and, similarly, for the Peltier heat generation at point \(l\).
The expressions for \(H_{\text {Pelt,VV, } \nu}\) and \(H_{\text {Pelt,VC }, v}\) are analogous to those for conduction band tunneling.

