\(V_{\text {ins }}\) is also treated in \(E_{\mathrm{C}}(\max )-E_{\mathrm{C}}(0)\), and \(E_{\mathrm{B} 0}\) is now used as the fitting parameter. Finally, \(E_{\mathrm{B}}\) is computed regardless of the sign of \(F_{\text {ins }}\) :
\[
E_{\mathrm{B}}=E_{\mathrm{C}}(\max )-E_{\mathrm{C}}(0)+E_{\mathrm{B} 0}-\alpha q\left|F_{\mathrm{ins}}\right|^{\frac{1}{2}}-\beta q\left|F_{\mathrm{ins}}\right|^{\frac{2}{3}}-P_{\perp} V_{\mathrm{sem}}
\]

