    me_10 = 0.914 # [1]
    me_t0 = 0.196 # [1]
}
```


Usually for III-V materials, the two-band \(\mathrm{k} \cdot \mathrm{p}\) model for \(\Delta_{2}\) valleys should not be used, and all valleys must be defined in the Multivalley section of the parameter file with all needed masses, energy shifts, deformation potentials, and so on. For some III-V materials such as

