\section*{Named Parameter Sets for Piezoresistance}

The Piezoresistance parameter set can be named. For example, in the parameter file, you can write the following to declare a parameter set with the name myset:
```
Piezoresistance "myset" { ... }
```


To use a named parameter set, specify its name with ParameterSetName as an option to Tensor as shown in the command file syntax (see Using Piezoresistance Mobility Model on page 1005).

By default, the unnamed parameter set is used.

\section*{Auto-Orientation for Piezoresistance}

The piezoresistance models support the auto-orientation framework (see Auto-Orientation Framework on page 91 ) that switches between different named parameter sets based on the orientation of the nearest interface. This can be activated by specifying AutoOrientation as an argument to Tensor in the command file.

