\section*{Analytic TEPower Model}

As an alternative, you can use analytic formulas as described in [13] and [14] to compute the thermoelectric powers in non-generate semiconductors:
\[
\begin{aligned}
P_{n} & =-\kappa_{n} \frac{k}{q}\left[\left(\frac{5}{2}-s_{n}\right)-\ln \left(\frac{n}{N_{c}(T)}\right)\right] \\
P_{p} & =\kappa_{p} \frac{k}{q}\left[\left(\frac{5}{2}-s_{p}\right)-\ln \left(\frac{p}{N_{v}(T)}\right)\right]
\end{aligned}
\]

For degenerate semiconductors where the Fermi correction is used, it is also possible to explicitly introduce the Fermi correction for the analytic thermoelectric powers as follows:
\[
\begin{aligned}
& P_{n}=-\kappa_{n} \frac{k}{q}\left[\left(\frac{5}{2}-s_{n}\right) \lambda_{n}-\ln \left(\frac{n}{N_{c}(T)}\right)+\ln \left(\gamma_{n}\right)\right] \\
& P_{p}=\kappa_{p} \frac{k}{q}\left[\left(\frac{5}{2}-s_{p}\right) \lambda_{p}-\ln \left(\frac{p}{N_{v}(T)}\right)+\ln \left(\gamma_{p}\right)\right]
\end{aligned}
\]
where \(\gamma_{n}\) and \(\gamma_{p}\) are described in Equation 48 and Equation 49, and \(\lambda_{n}\) and \(\lambda_{p}\) are described for Equation 66 and Equation 67. For Boltzmann statistics, \(\gamma_{n}=\gamma_{p}=\lambda_{n}=\lambda_{p}=1\). The Fermi correction must explicitly be enabled by using the keyword FermiForTEPAnalytic

