- XtRange specifies the start, end, and step size for defect locations, \(X_{t}\), along the path. The reference electrode is at \(X_{t}=0\). Defect locations, \(X_{t}\), cannot be closer than \(0.0001 \mu \mathrm{~m}\) to the electrodes, and the minimum-allowed step size is \(0.0001 \mu \mathrm{~m}\). If you do not specify XtRange, then \(X_{t}\) will span the entire path, from electrode to electrode, with a step size of \(0.0001 \mu \mathrm{~m}\).
- EtRange specifies the start, end, and step size for defect energy levels, \(E_{t}\), relative to the conduction band. The defect energy levels cannot be closer than 0.05 eV to the band edges, and the minimum-allowed step size is 0.05 eV . If you do not specify EtRange, then \(E_{t}\) will span the entire band gap with a step size of 0.05 eV .
