Tunneling Processes

or:
\[
\begin{aligned}
\text { factor }= & \text { SitesPerVolume } \text { × } \text { CellLength }{ }^{2} \text { (in two dimensions) } \\
& \times \text { AreaFactor }\left(\frac{10^{-4} \mathrm{~cm}}{\mu \mathrm{~m}}\right)^{3}
\end{aligned}
\]
where SitesPerVolume is an insulator property that is specified in the parameter file. The default is \(4.40 \mathrm{e} 22\left(\mathrm{SiO}_{2}\right), 5.54 \mathrm{e} 22\left(\mathrm{HfO}_{2}\right)\), and \(5.55 \mathrm{e} 22\left(\mathrm{ZrO}_{2}\right)\) in units of \(\# / \mathrm{cm}^{3}\).

\section*{TDDB Time-Step Management}

Specifying the UseKMCTimeStep option instructs Sentaurus Device to use the time step determined by the KMC simulator. The keyword MaxTrapNumberIncrease allows you to specify the maximum increment of the number of particles of each KMC time step. If the time required to generate the MaxTrapNumberIncrease of traps is shorter than the minimal transient time step defined in Transient\{MinStep=<float>\}, then the TDDB KMC routine is called repeatedly until the accumulated time surpasses the minimal time step or the simulation reaches its break criteria.

\section*{Note:}

The advance of time with respect to the event rate is a key component of the KMC algorithm. Setting MaxStep too low alters the simulation results when the maximum-allowed time interval is still too short for events to occur. Similarly, by setting Transient \(\{\) Plot() \(\}\) time steps, enforced time steps are added to the ramping sequence, which can also disrupt the KMC simulation. Use the time step callback function of the Python interface to write plot files around the given time steps without altering the simulation results (see Using Time Step Callback in Solve on page 1538).

\section*{TDDB Break Criteria}

Similar to other break criteria, the criteria to stop a TDDB simulation are defined in the Math\{BreakCriteria\{\}\} section and the Transient (BreakCriteria \{\}) statement. The keywords TDDBTrapNumber, TDDBCurrent, and TDDBCurrentRatio are stop criteria for the TDDB calculation, and only maxval is supported. For example:
