- MaxTrapNumberIncrease is 0 by default. Each time step allows a maximum number of particles to increase if UseKMCTimeStep is specified.
- TDDBTrapNumber is 0 by default. Use the value specified as the maximum trap number as a criterion to stop the TDDB calculation.
- TDDBCurrent is 0 by default with units of A. Use the value specified as the maximum current as a criterion to stop the TDDB calculation.
- TDDBCurrentRatio is 0 by default. Use the value specified as the maximum current ratio as a criterion to stop the TDDB calculation.

The current ratio is defined as \(\mathrm{I}(\mathrm{t}) / \min \left(\mathrm{I}\left(\mathrm{t}^{\prime}\right)\right.\) for \(\left.\mathrm{t}^{\prime}<\mathrm{t}\right)\).
The current stopping criteria work without UseKMCTimeStep and MaxTrapNumberIncrease, but the criteria work better when both of these are provided because more data points are sampled during the breakdown process.

