KMC Events

\section*{KMC Events}

Based on the defects defined, you can define KMC events (processes) during ReRAM operations. Table 189 lists the supported physical events.
Table 189 Supported physical events

\begin{tabular}{|l|l|l|}
\hline Physical event & Description & Relevant equation \\
\hline Diffusion & \begin{tabular}{l}
Keywords: Diffusion \\
A particle moves to a neighboring cell.
\end{tabular} & \(A\left(r_{1}\right) \rightarrow A\left(r_{2}\right)\) \\
\hline Bulk generation or recombination & \begin{tabular}{l}
Keywords: Generation, Recombination \\
One or two particle types are generated at a location or neighboring locations.
\end{tabular} & \(0 \Leftrightarrow A(r)+B(r)\) \\
\hline Interface generation or recombination & \begin{tabular}{l}
Keywords: Generation, Recombination \\
One or two particle types are generated or recombined at the interface. \\
For generation or recombination of two particles, the particles are located on different sides of the interface. \\
For generation or recombination of one particle, the particle is located on one side of the interface.
\end{tabular} & \(0 \Leftrightarrow A\left(r_{1}\right)+B\left(r_{2}\right)\) \\
\hline Filament growth or recession & \begin{tabular}{l}
Keywords: FilamentGrowth, FilamentRecession \\
Transition between particle and filament.
\end{tabular} & \(F(r) \Leftrightarrow A(r)\) \\
\hline
\end{tabular}

For the event rate, a generic expression is used:
\[
r=v \exp \left[-\frac{E_{\mathrm{A}}-p F}{k_{\mathrm{B}} T}\right]
\]
where:
- \(\quad v\) is the maximum rate of the event (keyword Frequency; default is 0.0 ).
- \(E_{\mathrm{A}}\) is the activation energy (keyword Ea ; default is 0.0 ).
- \(p\) is the molecular dipole (keyword Dipole; default is 0.0 ).
- \(F\) is the electric field.

The \(v, E_{\mathrm{A}}\), and \(p\) are parameters to be determined.

[Page 1184 END]
