\section*{Defect and Field Visualization}

You can set up the generation of particle plots of defects in the Plot section of the command file by using the ReRAMParticle option. The particle plots show the actual position of the defects within the Sentaurus Device structure when visualized with Sentaurus Visual.

When viewing the TDR file in Sentaurus Visual:
- The particles to be displayed can be chosen on the Lines/Particles tab of the Data Selection panel.
- The size and color of particles can be modified by choosing Data \(>\) Region Properties.

For example:
```
Plot {
    ...
    ReRAMParticle
    ReRAMPotential
    ReRAMTemperature
    ReRAMField
    ReRAMCurrent
}
```

where:
- ReRAMParticle specifies to output a discrete particle view of the ReRAM.
- ReRAMPotential specifies to output the potential to the TDR file.
- ReRAMTemperature specifies to output the temperature to the TDR file.
- ReRAMField specifies to output the electric field to the TDR file.
- ReRAMCurrent specifies to output the conductance current to the TDR file.

Figure 85 shows examples of visualization of output. For the input files, see ReRAM Example on page 1199.

