\section*{ReRAM Example}

For this example, the structure of the ReRAM is shown in Figure 85 (left). The ReRAM contains four layers: the top layer is \(\mathrm{HfO}_{2}\), the bottom layer is titanium, and the two thin layers in the middle are HfOx and TiOx . The two thin layers approximate an imperfect \(\mathrm{HfO}_{2}\) Ti interface. In this example, trap generation and recombination occur in the HfOx layer.

